One interpretation of this result is that a randomly chosen positive integer <i>n</i> has an average
number of divisors of about <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \ln n.}">
